body:
Thanks for the reviews, @ijuma  and @jozi-k.  I made some revisions, so check it out.

@ijuma, the exclusions for scala code are very necessary.  Findbugs does apparently trip up on some generated Scala code, and generate thousands of spurious warnings.

@jozi-k, there are tons of style cleanups we could do here.  I think we should focus on just getting findbugs clean here, and fixing things that are clearly bugs.  Then we can file follow-on JIRAs for any style cleanups that we feel like doing later.  This is part of the bigger effort of getting AK findbugs-clean so that we can enable findbugs-warnings-as-errors to prevent regressions.

@ijuma, you are right that the fact that TopicCount has no equals method, but one of its subclasses does, is a little suspicious.  I am re-running the unit tests with an equals method that throws an exception to see if the exception is ever thrown.
